          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Final Score: 7/10",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "heading",
        "tag": "h2",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "The Outbound Ghost",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " has been one of the more complicated reviews I've had to do in my time. There is a lot of potential here and in some areas, it really feels like Conradical Games have nailed the brief. However, it’s also a lesson in developer/publisher relationships and the pitfalls of porting a game across multiple platforms where the Nintendo Switch version often ends up neglected and compromised. However behind the cloak of bad-PR, I do believe there’s an enjoyable experience to be had by RPG fans, but maybe don’t play it on the Switch.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
